8 A Joint Resolution approving certain proposed
permanent rules of certain education state agencies;
9 and directing distribution.
10
11
12 WHEREAS, pursuant to Section 308 of Title 75 of the Oklahoma
13 Statutes, the Oklahoma State Legislature shall adopt a joint
14 resolution to approve or disapprove administrative rules.
15 NOW, THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES
16 AND THE SENATE OF THE 2ND SESSION OF THE 60TH OKLAHOMA LEGISLATURE:
17 SECTION 1. The Legislature hereby approves all proposed
18 permanent rules of the State Department of Education filed on or
19 before February 1, 2026.
20 SECTION 2. The Legislature hereby approves all proposed
21 permanent rules of the Office of Educational Quality and
22 Accountability filed on or before February 1, 2026.
23
24
ENGR. H. J. R. NO. 1088 Page 1

1 SECTION 3. The Legislature hereby approves all proposed
2 permanent rules of the State Regents for Higher Education filed on
3 or before February 1, 2026.
4 SECTION 4. The Legislature hereby approves all proposed
5 permanent rules of the Teachers' Retirement System filed on or
6 before February 1, 2026.
7 SECTION 5. The Legislature hereby approves all proposed
8 permanent rules of the Statewide Charter School Board filed on or
9 before February 1, 2026.
10 SECTION 6. The Legislature hereby approves all proposed
11 permanent rules of the Department of Career and Technology Education
12 filed on or before February 1, 2026.
13 SECTION 7. The Oklahoma Secretary of State is hereby directed
14 to distribute copies of this resolution to the Governor and the
15 editor of "The Oklahoma Register".
16 Passed the House of Representatives the 4th day of May, 2026.
